1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
I got a delivery for you.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,540
Leave it at reception.

3
00:00:08,540 --> 00:00:11,540
I'm supposed to deliver this one in person.

4
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Clean up on aisle five.

5
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:55,000
After three years of writing, one year of shooting, four years of reshooting, and two years of editing,

6
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:22,000
I have finally completed my movie, Threat Level Midnight.

7
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Yes?

8
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,000
What are you doing?

9
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:29,720
Guys, did you guys know that our own Michael Scott has made a movie and that he maybe will

10
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:33,000
let us watch it, but only if everybody's dying to see it?

11
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,000
That's, well, don't put words in my mouth.

12
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Threat Level Midnight is the great lost film of Michael Scott.

13
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,000
We're all in it from like years and years ago.

14
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,000
It's like a home movie.

15
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Yeah, if Michael Scott did your home movie.

16
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Michael screened a work in progress for us years ago, and it didn't go well.

17
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:55,000
We thought it was a comedy.

18
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Everything pointed to it being a comedy.

19
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,000
We'd love to see it.

20
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Sweet.

21
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:04,000
I will go invite Holly.

22
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Okay, everyone, I know we're really excited to see this movie that everybody's in, but

23
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:12,000
we have to remember that Michael is sensitive, so let's stay positive.

24
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:17,000
And no laughing, no comments, just positive energy, and we'll have a pure fun day.

25
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Okay?

26
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Thanks, Mom.

27
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,000
You never told me you made a movie.

28
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:24,000
It's got actions, it's got hearts, it's got symbolism.

29
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,000
It's got you.

30
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,000
It's got a lot of me.

31
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,000
I can't wait.

32
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Ladies and gentlemen, Threat Level Midnight.

33
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,000
Michael Scott?

34
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Well, that is an interesting story.

35
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:52,000
He was once the best secret agent in the business.

36
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
That was years ago.

37
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,000
Where is he now?

38
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Well, that's also an interesting story.

39
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Okay.

40
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Master Scarn.

41
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Master Scarn?

42
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:24,000
I play Samuel, Michael Scarn's robot butler.

43
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:30,000
I wanted Samuel's voice to be like this, but Michael thought that Samuel should be a very

44
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:35,000
advanced android, almost indistinguishable from a real person.

45
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Dwight does not play a robot.

46
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,000
I'm up.

47
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,000
It's the president.

48
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,000
He needs you for a mission.

49
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Tell him I'm retired.

50
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,000
It's golden phase.
